definition.value: A dicarboxylic acid consisting of fumaric acid having a methyl substituent at the 2-position.
A member of the class of  chloroethenes that is ethene substituted by chloro groups at positions 1, 1 and 2.
A cyclic hydroxamic acid that is  DIMBOA attached to a beta-D-glucopyranosyl residue at position 2 via a glycosidic linkage.
